Load necessary packages

For loading the raster data raster package

library(raster)
## Loading required package: sp

Load a single band raster

# load a single band
img <- raster('./data/LC09_L2SP_196025_20221206_20221208_02_T2_SR_B1.tif')

# display the attributes of the loaded raster
img
## class      : RasterLayer 
## dimensions : 8061, 7991, 64415451  (nrow, ncol, ncell)
## resolution : 30, 30  (x, y)
## extent     : 277185, 516915, 5449485, 5691315  (xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax)
## crs        : +proj=utm +zone=32 +datum=WGS84 +units=m +no_defs 
## source     : LC09_L2SP_196025_20221206_20221208_02_T2_SR_B1.TIF 
## names      : LC09_L2SP_196025_20221206_20221208_02_T2_SR_B1

Plot a single band

# plot a single band
plot(img)

# histogram of the raster image
hist(img, main = 'Distribution of pixel values', col = 'purple', maxpixels = ncell(img))

Loading multiple bands

# create the list of source files containg landsat 7 bands
landsat <- paste0('./data/LC09_L2SP_196025_20221206_20221208_02_T2_SR_B',
                  1:7,
                  '.tif')

# display the list created above
landsat
## [1] "./data/LC09_L2SP_196025_20221206_20221208_02_T2_SR_B1.tif"
## [2] "./data/LC09_L2SP_196025_20221206_20221208_02_T2_SR_B2.tif"
## [3] "./data/LC09_L2SP_196025_20221206_20221208_02_T2_SR_B3.tif"
## [4] "./data/LC09_L2SP_196025_20221206_20221208_02_T2_SR_B4.tif"
## [5] "./data/LC09_L2SP_196025_20221206_20221208_02_T2_SR_B5.tif"
## [6] "./data/LC09_L2SP_196025_20221206_20221208_02_T2_SR_B6.tif"
## [7] "./data/LC09_L2SP_196025_20221206_20221208_02_T2_SR_B7.tif"
# create raster stack
landsat_stack <- stack(landsat)

# display the attributes of the created raster stack
landsat_stack
## class      : RasterStack 
## dimensions : 8061, 7991, 64415451, 7  (nrow, ncol, ncell, nlayers)
## resolution : 30, 30  (x, y)
## extent     : 277185, 516915, 5449485, 5691315  (xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax)
## crs        : +proj=utm +zone=32 +datum=WGS84 +units=m +no_defs 
## names      : LC09_L2SP//2_T2_SR_B1, LC09_L2SP//2_T2_SR_B2, LC09_L2SP//2_T2_SR_B3, LC09_L2SP//2_T2_SR_B4, LC09_L2SP//2_T2_SR_B5, LC09_L2SP//2_T2_SR_B6, LC09_L2SP//2_T2_SR_B7
# create raster brick from the stacked layer
landsat_brick <- brick(landsat_stack)

# display the attributes of the raster brick
landsat_brick
